Standard and Poor's Corp said it placedon creditwatch with negative implications Mack Trucks Inc's 140mln dlrs of BB-plus senior debt.    S and P said Mack lost significant market share in heavyduty trucks last year. Through the nine months ended September30, 1986, the company's pretax loss before restructuring costs,equity income and extraordinary items widened to 30 mln dlrsfrom 23 mln dlrs in the year earlier period, it noted.    S and P withdrew the BB-plus ratings on the unit MackFinancial Corp's 9-5/8 pct debentures due 1990 and 9-3/4 pctdebentures of 1991 as they were called for redemption. Reuter&#3;